obfuscation: of course myself 'm of course; as it was awful large, as the biggest fish myself ever saw, and even of Russia we do not have aforesaid large fish as whale, and daddy Mike saw it too, and sure and I did.
original: Of course I'm sure. It was awful big. The biggest fish I ever saw. Even in Russia we do not have such big fish as whales. Paddy Mike saw it, too. Sure and I did.

obfuscation: also me two eyes almost fell out of me head with looking ' at it it was this wonderful.
original: And me two eyes nearly fell out of me head with lookin' at it, it was that wonderful.

obfuscation: He shot big stream in water right up out in his chief he did and then he dived down in the ocean repeatedly also our own serves did not see him any more at all at everything; there!
original: He shot a big stream of water right up out of his head, he did, and then he dived down in the ocean again, and we didn't see him any more at all, at all. There!

obfuscation: Now of you get to view the great large whale that 're almost as good as having former Saint Nicholas come ai n't it, yet whale ca not bring you no Christmas gifts can they linked, as und whale you can view any time.
original: Now if you get to see the great big whale, that's almost as good as having old Saint Nicholas come, ain't it? Whales can't bring you no Christmas presents, can they, Klinker? Und whales you can see any time.

obfuscation: I 'd rather have Saint Nicholas would n't I Schwillie Willie Winkum; yet which be this Saint Nicholas they 're looking for tula, why do not you knows which he is yet, he 's best former man this ever was.
original: I'd rather have Saint Nicholas, wouldn't I, Schwillie Willie Winkum? Who is this Saint Nicholas they are looking for, Hulda? Why, don't you know who he is yet? He's the best old man that ever was.

obfuscation: Und he comes night before Christmas und visits all the little children in Holland; as und in Germany too, and und if they are good they get sweet(s) und oranges und toys und things do not they Schwillie Willie Winkum?
original: Und he comes the night before Christmas und visits all the little children in Holland. Und in Germany, too. Und if they're good they get candy und oranges und toys und things, don't they, Schwillie Willie Winkum?

obfuscation: Und if they are bad they get a good large birch stick; but I ai n't been bad; and i have been awfully good be not I linked, as sure, und me also.
original: Und if they're bad, they get a good big birch stick. But I ain't been bad. I've been awfully good, isn't I, Klinker? Sure. Und me also.

obfuscation: On Christmas Eve inside Holland all the children march around streets following one which carries large silver movie star, and and the people who meet america give america money also donations to help poor people; and oh Christmas time be just grand inside Holland; as und our own serves set out our needle wooden shoes und old Saint Nicholas fills 'em along candy.
original: On Christmas Eve in Holland all the children march around the streets, following one who carries a big silver star. And the people who meet us give us money and gifts to help the poor. Oh, Christmas time is just grand in Holland! Und we set out our leedle wooden shoes und old Saint Nicholas fills 'em with candy.
